WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.670 --> 00:00:09.260
It's that dreaded time of year again.

2
00:00:10.130 --> 00:00:14.640
Health checkups start to get scary 
around this age.

3
00:00:15.010 --> 00:00:17.060
Oho?

4
00:00:17.060 --> 00:00:22.770
The heck, man? You had nothing 
lower than a B in last year's checkup.

5
00:00:22.770 --> 00:00:25.360
Did you get any warnings, Suzuki?

6
00:00:26.280 --> 00:00:28.440
Uric acid and neutral fat levels.

7
00:00:28.440 --> 00:00:30.780
Tends to happen with salespeople.

8
00:00:30.780 --> 00:00:35.160
However! I'm a different man this year!

9
00:00:35.160 --> 00:00:38.410
Because ever since last year's checkups,

10
00:00:38.410 --> 00:00:41.960
I've been eating healthy lunches 
made by my dear Keiko-chan!

11
00:00:43.210 --> 00:00:44.920
Ta-da!

12
00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:47.380
That's a lot of food.

13
00:00:47.920 --> 00:00:50.170
You got it. I'll do my best!

14
00:00:52.300 --> 00:00:55.260
Man, talk about love. This is pure love.

15
00:00:55.260 --> 00:00:57.350
Sure is!

16
00:00:57.350 --> 00:00:59.850
To live up to her love,

17
00:00:59.850 --> 00:01:02.940
I'm going to stop drinking and 
smoking until the health checkup.

18
00:01:02.940 --> 00:01:04.610
Time to eat.

19
00:01:05.190 --> 00:01:07.440
Drinking I get, but smoking, too?

20
00:01:07.780 --> 00:01:13.030
Aye. I want to live a long life 
together with Keiko-chan.

21
00:01:19.700 --> 00:01:22.500
I gotta chew my food well.

22
00:01:28.710 --> 00:01:31.010
That'll be 1,160 yen.

23
00:01:31.010 --> 00:01:31.920
Right.

24
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:38.850
Here's your change and receipt.

25
00:01:40.470 --> 00:01:42.230
Also, here.

26
00:01:42.600 --> 00:01:46.810
There's a new brand of non-alcoholic 
beer out with a promotional discount.

27
00:01:46.810 --> 00:01:47.900
Use it, if you'd like.

28
00:01:47.900 --> 00:01:50.480
Oh, thank you.

29
00:01:50.860 --> 00:01:53.450
I have a health checkup coming up soon,

30
00:01:53.450 --> 00:01:56.620
so I've been thinking about switching 
to non-alcoholic drinks for a bit.

31
00:01:56.620 --> 00:01:57.990
This will help.

32
00:01:57.990 --> 00:01:59.910
Oh?

33
00:03:45.140 --> 00:03:46.890
Good evening, Tayama-san.

34
00:03:46.890 --> 00:03:51.400
Hey, look who's here to smoke even 
though he has a health checkup soon.

35
00:03:51.400 --> 00:03:51.900
Huh?

36
00:03:52.150 --> 00:03:54.690
H-How do you know about that?

37
00:03:56.240 --> 00:03:58.320
Yamada-san told you?

38
00:03:58.320 --> 00:04:01.780
Yeah, yeah, I heard from Yamada-san.

39
00:04:01.780 --> 00:04:03.280
Sa-slow-ki.

40
00:04:04.080 --> 00:04:07.450
Yeah, it's real soon.

41
00:04:07.450 --> 00:04:10.920
I've reduced my daily count, okay?

42
00:04:11.630 --> 00:04:12.920
Pardon me.

43
00:04:12.920 --> 00:04:16.760
Reduced by what, one or two at most?

44
00:04:17.510 --> 00:04:19.300
Well... yes.

45
00:04:25.970 --> 00:04:29.640
Do supermarket employees 
get health checkups, too?

46
00:04:29.640 --> 00:04:33.440
Yeah. Ours will probably 
also come up pretty soon.

47
00:04:34.400 --> 00:04:38.820
Will you cut down before that too, then?

48
00:04:38.820 --> 00:04:40.820
Cut down...

49
00:04:43.870 --> 00:04:45.910
I'll only drink one spoonful of the broth.

50
00:04:47.080 --> 00:04:47.910
Of course.

51
00:04:47.910 --> 00:04:49.250
Wow!

52
00:04:49.910 --> 00:04:52.580
Health is wealth, after all.

53
00:04:52.580 --> 00:04:55.250
If we don't take care of our health, 
we won't be able to work.

54
00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:58.590
Way to go. You're so cool, Tayama-san.

55
00:04:59.170 --> 00:05:02.340
On the other hand, 
look at me and my pathetic self.

56
00:05:03.090 --> 00:05:06.970
I'm trying stopgap measures 
instead of just quitting beer for a while.

57
00:05:06.970 --> 00:05:10.730
And yet you've got a lotta food today.

58
00:05:10.730 --> 00:05:16.230
Oh, the doctors tell me every year 
to gain some weight.

59
00:05:17.690 --> 00:05:21.450
But I have a hard time keeping it on.

60
00:05:21.450 --> 00:05:25.530
Wish I could put on weight more easily.

61
00:05:24.950 --> 00:05:25.530
Yoink.

62
00:05:26.620 --> 00:05:27.870
Wh-What was that for?

63
00:05:27.870 --> 00:05:30.410
You really are all skin and bones.

64
00:05:30.410 --> 00:05:32.410
T-Tayama-san?

65
00:05:32.410 --> 00:05:36.750
Our deli section has the good stuff. 
Eat lots of it and gain weight.

66
00:05:37.380 --> 00:05:39.670
O-Okay, thanks.

67
00:05:40.840 --> 00:05:41.800
Well...

68
00:05:42.090 --> 00:05:45.140
I haven't been able to quit 
the single most harmful thing,

69
00:05:45.140 --> 00:05:47.470
so everything might as well be stopgap.

70
00:05:47.470 --> 00:05:49.680
Well, duh.

71
00:05:51.180 --> 00:05:54.940
But what if the doctors 
tell you to quit smoking?

72
00:05:55.270 --> 00:05:57.110
Would you quit?

73
00:05:57.110 --> 00:05:57.860
Huh?

74
00:06:00.320 --> 00:06:02.740
Well, uh...

75
00:06:03.450 --> 00:06:05.200
If I have to quit,

76
00:06:05.200 --> 00:06:08.160
that might be a problem.

77
00:06:09.200 --> 00:06:10.450
After all,

78
00:06:11.450 --> 00:06:13.080
the chief—

79
00:06:11.450 --> 00:06:13.080
Your boss...

80
00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:15.870
will still be hurling abuses at you.

81
00:06:17.460 --> 00:06:20.460
Yeah, and I don't think 
I'd be able to take it.

82
00:06:21.550 --> 00:06:24.970
Yeah, I might have 
a hard time quitting, too.

83
00:06:24.970 --> 00:06:28.100
I'd be done for if that happened.

84
00:06:30.970 --> 00:06:32.350
It's all good.

85
00:06:33.980 --> 00:06:37.600
There. Now you have an invincible body.

86
00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:45.530
Thanks.

87
00:06:47.110 --> 00:06:51.740
I feel like I've been overthinking 
all this cutting-down nonsense.

88
00:06:51.740 --> 00:06:54.460
I've come back to my senses now,

89
00:06:55.540 --> 00:06:57.500
and it's all thanks to Tayama-san...

90
00:07:07.840 --> 00:07:11.470
I'd have to... of course.

91
00:07:54.430 --> 00:07:56.430
Yahoo!

92
00:07:56.730 --> 00:08:00.980
My uric acid and neutral fats 
are within normal levels! I got an A!

93
00:08:01.400 --> 00:08:04.440
Wait, why have I gained weight 
since last year, though?

94
00:08:04.820 --> 00:08:08.360
Whatever! I need to tell Keiko-chan!

95
00:08:08.360 --> 00:08:09.280
Snappity snap.

96
00:08:09.280 --> 00:08:11.700
Tell me how yours came out later!

97
00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:13.830
I'm going for a smoke!

98
00:08:21.330 --> 00:08:23.380
What's up?

99
00:08:23.380 --> 00:08:25.340
How'd your checkup go?

100
00:08:29.220 --> 00:08:31.800
What's wrong? Did your shitty boss 
do something again?

101
00:08:32.470 --> 00:08:36.720
No. It's my body that's shitty.

102
00:08:36.720 --> 00:08:37.520
Wha?

103
00:08:38.100 --> 00:08:39.890
Tayama-san, uh...

104
00:08:41.060 --> 00:08:44.570
Smoking really is bad for you, huh?

105
00:08:50.150 --> 00:08:54.450
Sasaki-kun's checkup told him 
to get scanned and treated?

106
00:08:54.450 --> 00:08:55.370
For his lungs?

107
00:08:55.870 --> 00:08:57.660
I'm sorry for his loss.

108
00:08:58.120 --> 00:09:00.620
So he's going to quit smoking.

109
00:09:00.620 --> 00:09:02.080
Of course he would.

110
00:09:04.170 --> 00:09:06.130
What, Yamada?

111
00:09:06.880 --> 00:09:10.880
He won't have a reason 
to show up back there anymore.

112
00:09:13.430 --> 00:09:14.430
Yamada.

113
00:09:14.970 --> 00:09:18.890
If Sasaki-kun found out that someone 
had a surprising side to them,

114
00:09:19.220 --> 00:09:21.890
is he the kind of guy who 
wouldn't be able to accept it?

115
00:09:21.890 --> 00:09:24.060
He's not like that.

116
00:09:24.060 --> 00:09:25.730
Then all you need to say is,

117
00:09:25.730 --> 00:09:28.860
"It's actually me you always 
see at register two."

118
00:09:29.480 --> 00:09:31.900
Then you won't need a pretext 
to see each other.

119
00:09:33.570 --> 00:09:34.410
Well...

120
00:09:34.740 --> 00:09:38.160
His ideal image of Yamada-san 
the goddess will crumble to dust,

121
00:09:38.160 --> 00:09:41.200
but only because he'll start 
seeing you for who you are.

122
00:09:43.670 --> 00:09:47.460
Hey, Yamada? Are you listenin' to me?

123
00:09:46.250 --> 00:09:47.960
Excuse me.

124
00:09:47.460 --> 00:09:49.630
Yes, how may I help you?

125
00:09:49.630 --> 00:09:51.720
I was hoping to get this wrapped.

126
00:09:51.720 --> 00:09:53.300
Of course. Right away.

127
00:09:57.720 --> 00:09:59.890
I know that.

128
00:10:01.390 --> 00:10:02.640
So why...

129
00:10:06.230 --> 00:10:08.270
Why am I freaking out?

130
00:10:14.150 --> 00:10:16.950
I finally get a day off.

131
00:10:16.950 --> 00:10:19.240
Guess I'll go to the hospital tomorrow.

132
00:10:24.370 --> 00:10:26.880
I'll need to stop by and say 
goodbye sometime, too.

133
00:10:31.960 --> 00:10:33.760
T... Tayama-san?!

134
00:10:33.760 --> 00:10:35.550
Do you have plans now?

135
00:10:35.550 --> 00:10:37.930
Huh? No, nothing.

136
00:10:37.930 --> 00:10:39.760
Come with me, then.

137
00:10:47.190 --> 00:10:48.060
Oh.

138
00:10:50.360 --> 00:10:53.440
Go ahead and smoke, Tayama-san.

139
00:10:53.690 --> 00:10:59.160
I'd like to chew on this and smoke 
vicariously through you one last time.

140
00:10:59.160 --> 00:11:00.830
Oh, yeah?

141
00:11:09.670 --> 00:11:12.380
Are you really gonna be able 
to quit like that?

142
00:11:13.050 --> 00:11:14.970
I'm not very confident.

143
00:11:15.340 --> 00:11:16.760
Do you think I can?

144
00:11:17.930 --> 00:11:19.930
Don't ask me.

145
00:11:23.220 --> 00:11:24.600
Tayama-san.

146
00:11:26.850 --> 00:11:30.900
Thanks for inviting me 
back here back then.

147
00:11:32.190 --> 00:11:36.650
We probably won't have the chance 
to talk like this anymore,

148
00:11:37.400 --> 00:11:40.620
but if you happen 
to see me in the store...

149
00:11:41.780 --> 00:11:42.990
Don't say any more.

150
00:11:44.370 --> 00:11:48.790
Sasaki-san, I need to tell you something.

151
00:11:53.670 --> 00:11:54.670
Oh, sorry.

152
00:11:54.670 --> 00:11:55.460
Take it.

153
00:11:55.460 --> 00:11:57.010
O-Okay.

154
00:11:58.840 --> 00:12:01.340
Hello? Sasaki here.

155
00:12:01.340 --> 00:12:02.050
Yes.

156
00:12:02.510 --> 00:12:04.720
Right, my checkup results?

157
00:12:05.180 --> 00:12:08.270
I was thinking of going 
for scans tomorrow.

158
00:12:08.640 --> 00:12:09.270
Huh?

159
00:12:09.770 --> 00:12:10.520
What?

160
00:12:12.310 --> 00:12:14.610
Okay, I understand.

161
00:12:15.900 --> 00:12:17.280
Goodbye.

162
00:12:29.660 --> 00:12:31.580
It was a misdiagnosis.

163
00:12:33.170 --> 00:12:37.300
Apparently, my organs 
are very healthy for my age.

164
00:12:40.800 --> 00:12:42.260
I'm sorry!

165
00:12:43.510 --> 00:12:45.180
I'm happy for you!

166
00:12:45.680 --> 00:12:47.850
Sorry! I'm sorry, Tayama-san!

167
00:12:47.850 --> 00:12:49.940
Boy, am I glad to hear it.

168
00:12:49.180 --> 00:12:51.310
I made you worry for nothing!

169
00:12:49.940 --> 00:12:52.020
So very glad.

170
00:12:51.310 --> 00:12:53.190
I'm really sorry.

171
00:12:52.400 --> 00:12:54.020
Good for you.

172
00:12:54.520 --> 00:12:56.820
I'm so glad, though.

173
00:12:57.820 --> 00:13:01.910
I can keep smoking with you, huh?

174
00:13:06.910 --> 00:13:11.250
Oh, right. You said you wanted 
to tell me something.

175
00:13:11.250 --> 00:13:12.670
Sorry I cut you off.

176
00:13:13.290 --> 00:13:14.960
Could you tell me now?

177
00:13:23.090 --> 00:13:24.140
It's okay.

178
00:13:26.010 --> 00:13:27.760
It doesn't have to be now.

179
00:13:29.520 --> 00:13:30.730
So...

180
00:13:32.480 --> 00:13:34.770
Let's keep smoking together.

181
00:13:36.610 --> 00:13:40.360
Don't think I'm letting you off easy 
for winding me up like that, though.

182
00:13:40.360 --> 00:13:43.660
Y-Yeah, I'm sorry about that.

183
00:13:43.660 --> 00:13:47.030
But I do appreciate your concern.

184
00:13:47.530 --> 00:13:48.330
Hmph.
